The paper deals with lower bounds on randomized multiparty communication complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problems studied involve bit-vectors and graphs, which are common objects in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.CG). The paper also uses information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM) techniques.
